Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1} and discard. Halve
lengthways, then thinly slice. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{4} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on
medium heat.

> If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the leek and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring
occasionally, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If you prefer hob cooking your risotto, skip the oven and just use a normal
> pan.

Add the garlic to the leek pan. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @Risotto Rice{175%grams}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are
translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{20%grams} and @Boiled Water for the Risotto{600%milliliter}. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover
with foil).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water
has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> For hob cooking, pour in water a third at a time, 20-25 mins in total.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @Chives{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (use scissors if
easier).

Zest and halve the @Lemon{1}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine half the lemon juice with the @Sugar for the
Dressing{½%tsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Set aside.

Slice the remaining lemon into wedges.

When the risotto has 10 mins left, drain the @Scallops{200%grams}. Pat dry with
#kitchen paper{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When
hot, add the scallops and cook until golden and piping hot, ~{3%minutes} on both
sides.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw shellfish. The
> scallops are cooked when opaque in the middle.

When the scallops have 1 min left, add half the @Butter{40%grams}. Stir well to
combine.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the
@Peas{120%grams}, lemon zest, half the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams}
and the remaining butter.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lemon juice if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Add the @Wild Rocket{40%grams} and @Pumpkin Seeds{15%grams} to the #bowl{} of
dressing. Toss to coat the leaves.

Share the risotto between #bowls{} and top with the scallops, spooning over the
melted butter from the frying pan.

Sprinkle with the remaining cheese along with the chives and
@Chilli Flakes{1%pinch}.

Serve with the rocket salad and any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Enjoy!